This open source Android application allows you to stream GPX files through the Mock Location provider to simulate GPS on the device. 

Getting Started
===============
1.	Install "OI File Manager" on android device. 
		https://market.android.com/details?id=org.openintents.filemanager
2.	Install AndroidMockGpx application.
		adb install -g app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk
3.	Enable "mock locations" on Android device.
		Settings > Developer Options > Allow Mock Locations
		or
		Settings > System > Advanced > Developer Options > Allow Mock Locations
	On newer Android versions this has been replaced with an application selection.
		Settings > System > Advanced > Developer Options > Select mock location app
4.	Play gpx/gps file.


